<span id="freeTextContainer3809990814422400847">3.5 Stars. A good crime mystery with an eerie Jack The Ripper <i>copycat</i> connection to the murder&apos;s committed over a decade ago. About one third of the way in, I <u>could not</u> put the book down thinking 5 stars all the way, but then the focus of the murder investigation changed and my interest ebbed a bit. Still enjoyed it, but am hoping Detective Lacey Flint will be more convincing in her role in book #2 with a greater developed relationship to Joesbury.<p>I know I&apos;m in the minority with my rating, but s</p></span>
  <span id="freeText3809990814422400847" style="display:none">3.5 Stars. A good crime mystery with an eerie Jack The Ripper <i>copycat</i> connection to the murder's committed over a decade ago. About one third of the way in, I <u>could not</u> put the book down thinking 5 stars all the way, but then the focus of the murder investigation changed and my interest ebbed a bit. Still enjoyed it, but am hoping Detective Lacey Flint will be more convincing in her role in book #2 with a greater developed relationship to Joesbury.<p>I know I'm in the minority with my rating, but still look forward to seeing what happens next. </p></span>
